Chapter 3: Input/Output
- Stream: Sequence (stream) of bytes from source to destination
- Input stream: Sequence of characters from an input device to the computer
- Output stream: Sequence of characters from the computer to an output device
- Use iostream header file to extract/receive data from keyboard and send the ouitput to the screen
+ Syntax: #include <iostream>
- Contains definitions of two data types (istream & ostream)
- Contains cin & cout (C-input; C-output)
- Cin and the Extraction Operator:
+ Syntax: cin >> Variable >> Variable >> …;
+ When scanning, >> skips all leading whitespace
+ For some data types, if input is provided until an invalid value for that type, >> will stop input and will store it for the next variable
- Using Predefined Functions in a Program
+ Function (subprogram): a set of instructions when activated, accomplish a task
+ main() executes when a program is run
+ Other functions execute only when called
- Cin and the get function
+ The get function inputs next character (include whitespace)
+ Syntax: cin.get(VarChar)
- In C++, dot is the member access operator
- Cin and the ignore function
+ Ignore discards a portion of the input
+ Syntax: cin.ignore(IntExp. CharExp);
- Cin and the putback function
+ Putback places character back to the input stream
+ Syntax: cin.putback(VarChar);
- Cin and the peek function
+ Peek returns next character from the input stream, without removing the character from that stream
+ Syntax: VarChar = cin.peek();
- Input for the string type
+ The function getline reads until the end of the current line
+ Syntax: getline(cin, VarStr);
- Output and formatting output
+ Syntax: cout << Expression << Manipulator << …;
+ Manipulator is used to format the output
+ Escape sequences are used to display characters that have a special meaning in C++ or in an output statement, aka (\n; \t; \b; \r; \\; \”; \’)
- Setprecision manipulator
+ Output decimal numbers with up to n decimal places
+ Syntax: setprecision(n)
+ Must include the header #include <iomanip>
- Fixed and scientific manipulator
+ fixed outputs floating point numbers in a fixed decimal format
+ Syntax: cout << fixed;
+ scientific outputs floating point numbers in scientific format
+ Syntax: cout << scientific;
- Setting and resetting manipulators
+ Explicitly setting an I/O stream flag/manipulator:
+ Syntax: 
cout << manipulator;
cout << setiosflags(ios_base::manipulator);
+ Explicitly resetting an I/O stream flag/manipulator
cout.unsetf(ios::manipulator);
cout << resetiosflags(ios_base::manipulator)
- Showpoint manipulator
+ Showpoint forces output to show the decimal point and trailing zeros
+ Syntax: cout << showpoint;
- Setw manipulator
+ Outputs the value of an expression in specific columns
+ Output of the expression is right justified
+ Syntax: setw(n)
- Setfill manipulator
+ Output stream variables can use setfill to fill unused columns with a character
+ Syntax: setfill(ch)
- Left and right manipulators
+ Syntax: cout << left; cout << right;
- Types of manipulators:
+ Parameterized: with parameters require iomanip and iostream
+ Non-parameterized: without parameters (only requires iostream)
- File I/O:
1. #include <fstream>
2. ifstream FilestreamVariable; (or ofstream FilestreamVariable;)
3. FilestreamVariable.open(SourceFileName, Mode);
4. Use << or >> to do input or output function
5. FilestreamVariable.close();
